#### Description

A basic Japanese de-inflection engine based on the Rikai Firefox plugin.
Returns an array of possible variants using the 'deinflect' instance method.

#### Usage Example

    #import "Deinflector.h"

    NSArray *variants;
    
    Deinflector *deinflector = [[Deinflector alloc] init];
    variants = [deinflector deinflect:word];

    // Log the deinflected variants of the word
    for (DeinflectorRuleMatch *variant in variants) {
      NSLog(@"Deinflected variant: %@", [variant word]);
    }
    
#### Dependencies

1. LWE Development Tools for custom logging (or just remove NSLog calls).
2. Deinflection rules from the Rikaichan Firefox add-on by J. Zarate (LGPL, www.polarcloud.com)

NB: GTMSenTest is needed for testing, but you won't not need it unless you're creating RikaiKit Tests!
